        "description": {
            "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> You or an ally within range attempts a saving throw.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You twist the forces of fate to make a moment dire or uneventful, with no in-between.</p>\n<p>The target gains a +1 status bonus to the triggering saving throw. If the saving throw's result is a success, it becomes a critical success. If it's a failure, it becomes a critical failure, and the critical failure can't be reduced by abilities that usually reduce critical failure, such as improved evasion.</p>\n<p>If the triggering ability did not have both a critical success and critical failure condition, tempt fate fails, but you don't expend the Focus Point for Casting this Spell.</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spell-effects.Spell Effect: Tempt Fate]{Spell Effect: Tempt Fate}</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Heightened (8th)</strong> The bonus on the saving throw is +2.</p>"
